##! Please refer to the documentation at
##! https://coreruleset.org/docs/development/regex_assembly/.

##! Django / ORM lookup operators, used as the trailing segment of a
##! filter key after the `__` separator. Shared by 934210 (PL3, any
##! operator suffix) and 934220 (PL2, operator suffix after nested
##! relationship traversal).
##!
##! Source: https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/6.0/ref/models/querysets/#field-lookups
##!
##! Deliberately EXCLUDED:
##!   - date/time transforms (date, year, iso_year, month, day, week,
##!     week_day, iso_week_day, quarter, time, hour, minute, second):
##!     these are common English words (high false-positive risk even with
##!     the `__` anchor) and have low attack value -- date extraction does
##!     not leak sensitive data or bypass authentication.
##!   - postgres contrib lookups (search, trigram_similar, unaccent, overlap):
##!     niche, contrib-only, and `search`/`overlap` are common words.
##! Revisit if a concrete bypass using any of these is reported.

##! string / comparison / null lookups
i?startswith
i?endswith
i?contains
i?exact
i?regex
isnull
range
gte?
lte?
in

##! JSONField lookups (key probing / containment)
has_key
has_keys
has_any_keys
contained_by
